Package model.weapons

Class Effect

  • java.lang.Object
    • model.weapons.Effect
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    EffectDamage, EffectMark, EffectMoveTarget, EffectMoveYourself
    public abstract class Effect
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.io.Serializable
    This is an abstract class that is used to create four children: EffectDamage, EffectMark, EffectMoveYourself, EffectMoveTarget, in which it is implemented the abstract method executeEffect(Match, MoveController, ShootingParametersInput). This class represents the possible effects a weapon can have.

    Riccardo

      • executeEffect

        public abstract void executeEffect​(Match match,
                                   MoveController ctrl,
                                   ShootingParametersInput input)
                            throws NotAllowedMoveException
        This method will execute the particular effect on which it will be called.
        Parameters:
        match - is the reference to the match
        ctrl - is the reference to the moveController
        input - is an instance of ShootingParametersInput
        Throws:
        NotAllowedMoveException - thrown only in the implementation of EffectMoveYourself and EffectMoveTarget
